/*C&$T*/ Compilable & Strictly Typed

Comment based system allowing type-less dynamic languages eg JavaScript to run normally, yet be all or partly type checked, easily translatable to, and compilable in, another off the shelf language eg Pawn, C or C++. Eases AOT ahead of time compilation eg by embedding a Pawn or Tiny C compiler into a browser's engine to create dynamically linkable code. Specific performance critical sections can be compiled, use SIMD, or complex sections can be strictly type checked. 

/*C&$T:1.0 (C) 2014 G.Symons All Rights Reserved Under FreeBSD License*/

/*C&$T:Compiler:JS2C:G.S.0.1*/
//Some compilers may only allow a subset of JS.

/*C&$T.On*/
/*ob.Pt {fp64 x,y;};*/
/*fn.fp64*/   function L2(/*r.ob.Pt*/o)
{
  /*fp64*/ l2=o.x*o.x+o.y*o.y;
  return l2;
}
/*C&$T.Off*/

